<TITLE> Pintu cleared in mugging case after charges dropped </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 3 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court on Monday acquitted BNP leader Nasiruddin Ahmed Pintu in a case involving mugging, beating and issuing threats after the plaintiff withdrew the charges, his lawyer said. The plaintiff, Mohammed Shahidul Islam, filed the case with Kamrangirchar Police Station against four and several unidentified people on Feb 13, 2007. He later in an affidavit told the court of Dhaka metropolitan magistrate Emdadul Huq that he had filed "false allegations" under pressure from "a particular group", lawyer Zoynal Abedin said. The court was to indict him on Monday. Pintu was present in the dock. The case details said on Feb 12 Pintu with his men had come to Islam's home and asked him why he had get 'Faruq member' arrested with arms. When Islam told him that he did not know anything about the matter, they had beaten him and snatched his gold chain, ring, cash and the mobile-phone set. Sub-inspector of Kamrangirchar Police Station pressed the charges on April 21. bd
